<br>
Clearly they deserve death by sand-paper.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=adrionakb>Adriona KB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/25/02 1:52:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3417.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Snipers ownd</span><hr size=1> There might be more :/<br>
<br>
Yeah, everyone is pretty sure it's them. But I  also heard they basically gave themselves up by telling police to check an old shooting sight for some clues. I dunno, you could think they gave themselves up too easy, in hopes of the police really easing up on the case some, maybe to have the other ones   -if there are- not arrested to something reaaally big soon after? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cyanravyn>Cyanravyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/25/02 2:00:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3417.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Snipers ownd</span><hr size=1> What's really sad and VERY scary about this whole thing, is that the this case is going to be in the court systems for YEARS. Appeal after appeal is going to make us the tax payers spend MILLIONS of dollars. Everyone deserves fair represntation right? Would you wanna be the counsel for these guys? I sure as heck wouldn't. Soon as they are convicted, it will go to appeals and MORE appeals. <br>
<br>
One of the things that I have learned about the United States is that unless you are a criminal you have no rights. Scary isn't it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilvensk>KilvenSK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/25/02 3:17:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3417.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Snipers ownd</span><hr size=1> Yes they were owned. Yes it did seem too easy. However it's over and they are in jail and that's what really matters.<br>
<br>
As far as the &quot;conspiracy theory&quot;. Um yeah sure,there are probally a horde of black men right now all hiding in their trunks waiting to put a cap in someone's ass. Better yet I can't wait for Bush to come out and state that the SniperMobile was created by Al Queda to aid their Muslim brothers in taking out some &quot;infidels&quot;. Some shit just is what it is IMHO. These two people just happened to be short on brains,long on luck and had WAY too much free time.<br>
<br>
As far as the appeal. Only some sort of technicality in the way they were brought in or the searching of the vehicle seems to be their only hope. From everything that I read outside of actually catching them in the act,there seems to be an infinitesmal amount of doubt that the authorities have the right people. I hope they spend the rest of their lives tossing the salads of all the other &quot;innocent&quot; men in their cell block.<br>
<br>
KilvenSK-InnoruuksBish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cyanravyn>Cyanravyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 301<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/25/02 6:55:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3417.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Snipers ownd</span><hr size=1> Kilven I can certainly agree with you on the "tossing salads" in prison. I am not one of those that supports the death penalty. Not cause I'm a bleeding heart, but becuase death isn't a punishment. It's the easy way out.<br>
<br>
However, that isn't what will happen. These two will go into protective custody. They dont' dare let them run in general population, the other prisoners would probably kill them. Prisoners have a relatively strange (by our understanding) moral code. But it is rigidly adhered too. Anyone who has ever worked for any prison is aware of that.<br>
<br>
Suggest you take a look at the appeals system. EVERY mass murder that has been caught hands down has appealed and managed to keep it in the court systems. Sad but true. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eyrit>Eyrit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/26/02 10:55:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3417.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Snipers ownd</span><hr size=1> Heh. I was watching CBC news and I loved the way the reporter described them, mind you it was unprofessional and a smack at the US of course. Paraphrasing what he said: &quot;Two losers effectively gripped several million people in fear. Imagine what a slightly more intelligent pair or organization could do&quot;. Not his exact words but he kept using 'losers' to describe them. I almost died laughing.<br>
